1
00:00:33,101 --> 00:00:36,455
TALK TO HER

2
00:03:26,360 --> 00:03:29,670
The stage is full of wooden
chairs and tables.

3
00:03:30,720 --> 00:03:34,075
Two women come out with robes.

4
00:03:34,519 --> 00:03:38,034
Their eyes are closed.
Like two sleepwalkers.

5
00:03:38,519 --> 00:03:42,591
You get scared...They trip
on everything, poor them.

6
00:03:42,918 --> 00:03:46,433
But suddenly, a man appears.

7
00:03:46,878 --> 00:03:51,349
With a very sad face, the
saddest I have ever seen.

8
00:03:51,838 --> 00:03:55,466
He pushes tables and chairs
out of their way.

9
00:03:57,357 --> 00:04:00,394
You can't imagine how touching
it was.

10
00:04:01,837 --> 00:04:05,431
Someone was sitting next to me.
In his 40s, hundsome.

11
00:04:06,516 --> 00:04:09,826
He cried with emotion,
lots of times.

12
00:04:10,116 --> 00:04:13,995
I don't understand why...
It was very beautiful!

13
00:04:15,555 --> 00:04:17,671
I have a surprise for you!

14
00:04:25,555 --> 00:04:28,830
I have an autograph of
Rina Baus for you.

15
00:04:29,114 --> 00:04:31,582
I had to buy the photo.

16
00:04:33,954 --> 00:04:36,314
It is in english and says:

17
00:04:36,314 --> 00:04:39,669
I hope you surpass all
the obstacles...

18
00:04:40,113 --> 00:04:42,468
... and start dancing.

19
00:05:07,151 --> 00:05:09,903
-She has her period.
-It's early.

20
00:06:18,264 --> 00:06:20,016
Good evening.

21
00:06:25,903 --> 00:06:28,576
Benigno, can you
stay tonight?

22
00:06:28,903 --> 00:06:32,179
My sister can't,
and I don't have anyone else.

23
00:06:32,423 --> 00:06:35,255
Why did you come?
You should have called.

24
00:06:35,342 --> 00:06:38,857
I am not taking advantage of you.
This week you did 3 nights.

25
00:06:39,182 --> 00:06:42,970
Don't worry. A free afternoon
is enough for me.

26
00:06:43,262 --> 00:06:46,776
I have to see the house
workers. It's a mess.

27
00:06:48,581 --> 00:06:51,101
And to frame a photo.

28
00:06:51,101 --> 00:06:55,413
My condition is not improving.
The hospital will decide.

29
00:06:55,901 --> 00:06:58,892
Your husband left you
and the children.

30
00:06:59,140 --> 00:07:02,769
Just come the nights you can.
We will be ok.

31
00:07:05,460 --> 00:07:07,450
Thanks a lot.

32
00:07:08,659 --> 00:07:12,015
-You cut off the intestinal food.
-She couldn't take it.

33
00:07:12,259 --> 00:07:15,410
-We will try again tomorrow.
-Yes, go now.

34
00:07:16,699 --> 00:07:18,609
And keep the spirits up!

35
00:07:25,658 --> 00:07:30,333
Six bulls and a woman.
Wednesday at Briuega.

36
00:07:31,497 --> 00:07:35,126
Lydia P Gonzales will
fight six bulls.

37
00:07:36,937 --> 00:07:39,609
Why such a drastic decision?

38
00:07:39,736 --> 00:07:43,251
It's my job. 2 bulls, or 6.
Whatever they say.

39
00:07:43,656 --> 00:07:46,896
People say a lot of bullfighters
won't fight with you...

40
00:07:46,896 --> 00:07:48,816
...because you are a woman.

41
00:07:48,816 --> 00:07:51,454
People can say what they want.

42
00:07:51,765 --> 00:07:55,155
Too much chauvinism in bullfighting,
but there are exceptions.

43
00:07:55,565 --> 00:08:00,320
Nino Valencia was happy to share
billing with you for several months.

44
00:08:03,284 --> 00:08:06,242
Do you think he did it
to promote himself?

45
00:08:06,604 --> 00:08:08,834
And when he succeeded that,
he abandoned you?

46
00:08:09,124 --> 00:08:12,035
I told you, I don't want
to talk about this!

47
00:08:12,363 --> 00:08:15,603
But by talking about
certain problems...

48
00:08:15,603 --> 00:08:18,123
...is the first step
towards their solution.

49
00:08:18,123 --> 00:08:20,717
-Nino Valencia...
-Enough!

50
00:08:21,083 --> 00:08:25,042
My dear Lydia, let me
finish the question.

51
00:08:25,042 --> 00:08:28,273
I am not discussing this.
I told you earlier.

52
00:08:28,402 --> 00:08:32,642
You didn't say anything earlier!
It's bad what you are saying!

53
00:08:32,642 --> 00:08:35,721
They will think
it's a fixed interview.

54
00:08:35,721 --> 00:08:39,509
And I am on of the few who
dare say the truth...

55
00:08:39,721 --> 00:08:42,681
...and you should dare accept

56
00:08:42,681 --> 00:08:45,877
...that Nino Valencia
took advantage of you.

57
00:08:46,280 --> 00:08:50,760
He shared with you not only
the fame, but sex as well.

58
00:08:50,760 --> 00:08:54,196
And he left you when
time was right.

59
00:08:55,559 --> 00:08:58,596
Juan Luis, Marco here...
How are you?

60
00:08:59,199 --> 00:09:01,349
I want to ask you something.

61
00:09:02,039 --> 00:09:05,475
I would like to do an article
about Lydia Gonzales.

62
00:09:06,398 --> 00:09:08,593
Yes, I see it too...

63
00:09:11,238 --> 00:09:13,991
I would like to do something
deep.

64
00:09:15,918 --> 00:09:19,068
For the Sunday issue?
Great...

65
00:10:13,032 --> 00:10:16,911
-The woman has gone crazy!
-She dedicates it to you.

66
00:10:17,312 --> 00:10:20,986
She would let the bull injur
her, just so that you see it.

67
00:10:21,511 --> 00:10:24,503
You shouldn't have come,
especially you.

68
00:11:13,427 --> 00:11:16,418
Don't tell me anything.
I know what I am doing.

69
00:11:16,866 --> 00:11:20,779
Nino should concentrate.
He doesn't want any more worries.

70
00:11:21,146 --> 00:11:25,025
Nothing to worry about. He should
just come to pick up his stuff.

71
00:11:25,745 --> 00:11:29,225
-Or tell me where to send them.
-Send them at my place.

72
00:11:29,225 --> 00:11:33,184
He, himself, should say so.
This is nothing to do with you.

73
00:11:35,625 --> 00:11:38,013
You can leave whenever you want.

74
00:11:38,344 --> 00:11:41,104
-Good evening.
-Scotch on the rocks, please.

75
00:11:41,104 --> 00:11:44,335
-What glass do you prefer?
-A tall one.

76
00:11:48,943 --> 00:11:51,935
Can I talk to you for
a minute, please?

77
00:11:53,623 --> 00:11:56,774
Forget it. When something is
over, it's over.

78
00:11:58,302 --> 00:12:01,931
-What are you saying?
-Can I talk to you?

79
00:12:04,742 --> 00:12:08,222
If you take me to Madrid,
we can talk on the way.

80
00:12:08,222 --> 00:12:10,337
It will be my pleasure.

81
00:12:23,020 --> 00:12:26,251
-Who named you Lydia;
-My father.

82
00:12:26,500 --> 00:12:29,617
It's as if he sealed your destiny.

83
00:12:29,740 --> 00:12:34,017
He always wanted to be a bullfighter,
but stayed a banderillero.

84
00:12:34,739 --> 00:12:38,414
He is the one that was there
for me, more than anyone else.

85
00:12:38,859 --> 00:12:41,167
But he died last year.

86
00:12:42,418 --> 00:12:44,409
I am sorry.

87
00:12:45,018 --> 00:12:48,408
'El Pais' wants me to do a profile
on you for their Sunday issue.

88
00:12:48,658 --> 00:12:52,013
Do you write on bullfighting?
I don't know your name.

89
00:12:52,217 --> 00:12:55,414
To be honest,
I know nothing of it.

90
00:12:56,617 --> 00:13:00,292
But I know a lot about
desperate women.

91
00:13:00,697 --> 00:13:03,972
And who told you I am
desperate?

92
00:13:04,296 --> 00:13:07,736
-This is the impression I have.
-Bullfighting doesn't interest you.

93
00:13:07,736 --> 00:13:10,808
You are interested in my
relationship with Nino Valencia.

94
00:13:11,056 --> 00:13:14,127
Tell EI Pais to leave me alone!

95
00:13:51,892 --> 00:13:54,452
-Take me from here!
-What's going on?

96
00:13:54,532 --> 00:13:58,206
Take me from here! There is
a snake in the kitchen.

97
00:13:58,491 --> 00:14:01,563
-Give me the keys.
-The door is open.

98
00:14:01,811 --> 00:14:04,041
Calm down.
And stay there.

99
00:15:34,202 --> 00:15:36,193
My purse.

100
00:15:38,042 --> 00:15:40,476
Take me to a hotel.

101
00:15:40,842 --> 00:15:43,515
I am never coming back to
this house.

102
00:15:44,241 --> 00:15:47,870
-To which hotel?
-To Eurobuilding, lets say.

103
00:16:16,478 --> 00:16:19,675
Don't tell anyone about
the snake, please.

104
00:16:20,558 --> 00:16:23,197
Only my family knows.

105
00:16:23,318 --> 00:16:26,549
I always respect other
people's phobias.

106
00:16:26,918 --> 00:16:31,035
After what you have done, how
can I say no to to the profile?

107
00:16:31,797 --> 00:16:35,756
Think about it again. I will
call tomorrow, tell me then.

108
00:16:36,557 --> 00:16:38,831
Thanks for everything.

109
00:17:01,074 --> 00:17:04,862
Do you want me to stay? I can
sleep in the sofa.

110
00:17:05,074 --> 00:17:08,225
No, I need to get used to
being alone.

111
00:17:49,150 --> 00:17:51,027
Do you wash her?

112
00:17:51,310 --> 00:17:53,187
What do you think?

113
00:17:53,869 --> 00:17:56,508
-How was the night?
-normal.

114
00:17:56,909 --> 00:18:00,458
-Give it to me. I will do it.
-I am going now.

115
00:18:00,669 --> 00:18:02,944
-Good bye.
-Bye, Matilde.

116
00:18:06,308 --> 00:18:08,299
It's so hot!

117
00:18:08,748 --> 00:18:12,297
-Lets cut her hair.
-short, it's more practical.

118
00:18:13,228 --> 00:18:16,264
We will leave it as it was
when she came here...

119
00:18:16,547 --> 00:18:19,427
...so that she is not surprised
when she wakes up.

120
00:18:19,427 --> 00:18:22,419
After 4 years, it will be great.

121
00:18:22,507 --> 00:18:24,987
I believe in miracles.
So should you.

122
00:18:24,987 --> 00:18:27,978
-Why me?
-Because you need them.

123
00:18:28,226 --> 00:18:32,265
One might happen to you,
and you will not know.

124
00:18:32,986 --> 00:18:35,022
So hot!

125
00:18:35,266 --> 00:18:37,345
I took something from the
drugstore...

126
00:18:37,345 --> 00:18:40,337
...to help stop the perspiration
stains on my uniform.

127
00:18:40,745 --> 00:18:44,185
My armpits are ok,
but look at my face.

128
00:18:44,185 --> 00:18:46,540
-What's it called?
-Perspirex.

129
00:18:54,944 --> 00:18:57,412
It's Marco...
Remember me?

130
00:18:58,183 --> 00:19:00,617
-How are you?
-Naked.

131
00:19:05,863 --> 00:19:08,740
I need to buy some clothes.
That's all I've got.

132
00:19:09,222 --> 00:19:11,690
I can bring you some
from your place.

133
00:19:12,062 --> 00:19:15,134
I don't want anything from there.
Maybe another time.

134
00:19:15,462 --> 00:19:17,578
-Where are we going?
-To Sybilla.

135
00:19:17,822 --> 00:19:20,289
-You think I am crazy.
-Why?

136
00:19:20,541 --> 00:19:24,011
-Because I don't want to go home.
-No, I understand.

137
00:19:24,461 --> 00:19:28,579
When I separated, I couldn't
sleep in the same bed...

138
00:19:28,941 --> 00:19:31,977
I was sleeping in the sofa,
in the living room.

139
00:19:32,180 --> 00:19:36,378
For a week. Until I finally
bought a new bed.

140
00:19:36,780 --> 00:19:38,896
So, you are separated.

141
00:19:39,660 --> 00:19:41,536
I am alone.

142
00:19:42,459 --> 00:19:46,088
AFTER A FEW MONTHS

143
00:20:03,257 --> 00:20:05,930
Marco, we should
talk afterwards.

144
00:20:06,257 --> 00:20:09,727
-We've been talking for an hour.
-You have, not me.

145
00:20:10,737 --> 00:20:12,648
Indeed.

146
00:20:40,214 --> 00:20:44,605
Did you read about the nuns
that got raped by the misionaries?

147
00:20:46,213 --> 00:20:49,967
Priests, themselves!
It's horrible!

148
00:20:50,453 --> 00:20:53,333
Yeah, they've gone bad too!
Where are we heading to?

149
00:20:53,333 --> 00:20:55,847
First they raped the locals.

150
00:20:56,253 --> 00:20:59,562
Then, due to AIDS, they started
raping nuns.

151
00:21:00,452 --> 00:21:03,125
And I admired them so much!

152
00:21:03,452 --> 00:21:06,091
Not all of them are rapists,
for sure.

153
00:21:06,412 --> 00:21:09,164
No, some of them are
pedophiles.

154
00:21:09,491 --> 00:21:13,166
-What's that? Everyone loves fucking.
-Antonio, you are an animal!

155
00:21:14,931 --> 00:21:17,922
-How do the bulls look?
-Good, but fat.

156
00:21:18,370 --> 00:21:21,487
-How much do you think?
-Over 500 kilos.

157
00:21:22,250 --> 00:21:25,959
I am going to the bar. And don't
forget, we are eating home.

158
00:21:26,250 --> 00:21:29,559
If the kids don't see their aunt,
there'll be hell to pay.

159
00:24:41,942 --> 00:24:44,614
Don't cry, my love.

160
00:24:54,140 --> 00:24:57,020
-How is it?
-Very bad.

161
00:24:57,020 --> 00:24:58,817
It tore her apart.

162
00:24:58,900 --> 00:25:01,420
The father will be happy now!

163
00:25:01,420 --> 00:25:05,617
'Not the little one!', we kept
telling him, my mother and I.

164
00:25:08,059 --> 00:25:10,859
And yet, she became like him.

165
00:25:10,859 --> 00:25:13,089
Don't be upset.

166
00:25:14,019 --> 00:25:16,134
What time is it?

167
00:25:16,378 --> 00:25:18,448
It has been four hours.

168
00:25:19,778 --> 00:25:22,611
AFTER THREE WEEKS

169
00:25:23,938 --> 00:25:26,057
Are you going to Cordoba?

170
00:25:26,057 --> 00:25:29,686
Yes...I would like to stay,
but I can't.

171
00:25:29,777 --> 00:25:33,213
We can't do anything extra.

172
00:25:33,337 --> 00:25:35,737
The bar's been closed for 20 days.

173
00:25:35,737 --> 00:25:39,172
The kids are with the neigbhour,
and I've neglected the other one.

174
00:25:39,456 --> 00:25:42,846
If something happens, can
you be here in 2 hours?

175
00:25:43,296 --> 00:25:47,288
-Rest assured for that.
-We have to have faith.

176
00:25:49,335 --> 00:25:51,975
I light some candles...

177
00:25:51,975 --> 00:25:54,887
...but I find it very
difficult to have faith.

178
00:25:55,575 --> 00:25:58,691
When can we put her medals
back on her?

179
00:25:59,694 --> 00:26:01,574
Not yet.

180
00:26:01,574 --> 00:26:05,692
With all these...
wounds, the tracheotomy...

181
00:26:08,614 --> 00:26:10,808
She never took them off.

182
00:26:24,452 --> 00:26:26,488
I will get a vase.

183
00:26:45,490 --> 00:26:48,607
I have to go to the US
for three months.

184
00:26:49,090 --> 00:26:52,161
It is very important,
says my agent.

185
00:26:52,489 --> 00:26:56,368
And yet...the way things
stand here...

186
00:26:59,169 --> 00:27:01,603
...I don't want to go.

187
00:27:14,247 --> 00:27:17,319
Can you get out for
a moment, please?

188
00:27:26,446 --> 00:27:29,438
No smoking here.

189
00:27:31,926 --> 00:27:34,121
Did she talk to you that day?

190
00:27:35,885 --> 00:27:39,195
-Or rather, I talked.
-And what did you say?

191
00:27:40,525 --> 00:27:42,595
Things that concern me.

192
00:27:43,365 --> 00:27:46,244
Did she tell you anything
about me?

193
00:27:46,244 --> 00:27:50,203
Honestly, Lydia hadn't talked
about you for a long time.

194
00:27:51,044 --> 00:27:55,401
-It's my fault for what happened.
-No, it's my fault.

195
00:31:52,582 --> 00:31:55,618
Caetano made me
freak out.

196
00:31:58,861 --> 00:32:02,376
Marco, I've always wanted
to ask you something.

197
00:32:02,621 --> 00:32:06,295
Why did you cry that night,
after you killed the snake?

198
00:32:08,020 --> 00:32:10,409
It brought me lots of memories.

199
00:32:12,100 --> 00:32:15,569
Years ago, I had to
kill another snake.

200
00:32:15,939 --> 00:32:18,055
We were in Africa.

201
00:32:18,499 --> 00:32:21,499
She had the same phobia as you.

202
00:32:21,499 --> 00:32:26,526
She was waiting outside the tent,
terrified, defenseless...

203
00:32:27,858 --> 00:32:30,088
...and totally naked...

204
00:32:31,738 --> 00:32:35,014
...because she had seen the snake,
while we were asleep.

205
00:32:35,378 --> 00:32:38,528
Was it the same one who made
you sleep in the living room?

206
00:32:40,857 --> 00:32:43,212
I hate that woman.

207
00:32:43,657 --> 00:32:47,176
-I haven't seen her for years.
-Even worse.

208
00:32:47,176 --> 00:32:50,168
What can I do to make you
forget her?

209
00:32:50,376 --> 00:32:52,731
Exactly what you are doing now.

210
00:33:22,293 --> 00:33:26,047
You were sound asleep. We didn't
want to wake you up.

211
00:33:27,933 --> 00:33:31,527
-Is Dr Vega here?
-He is in his office.

212
00:34:11,889 --> 00:34:14,960
Rosa, close the door.
There's a draft.

213
00:34:15,728 --> 00:34:18,845
-She opened her eyes.
-That gives me the creeps!

214
00:34:19,128 --> 00:34:22,165
-And when she yawns?
-I shit myself!

215
00:34:24,008 --> 00:34:27,124
Good morning, doctor.
I want to talk to you.

216
00:34:27,687 --> 00:34:29,962
How are you? Did you sleep well?

217
00:34:30,887 --> 00:34:32,479
I will buy you coffee.

218
00:34:34,127 --> 00:34:37,357
How long for might Lydia
stay like that?

219
00:34:37,606 --> 00:34:41,315
Months... years...
maybe for the rest of her life...

220
00:34:42,246 --> 00:34:44,601
There is no hope?

221
00:34:46,005 --> 00:34:49,441
As a doctor, I have to say
no... However...

222
00:34:49,725 --> 00:34:51,716
RESUSCITATION

223
00:34:52,085 --> 00:34:55,441
Meryl Moon wakes up after
15 years in a coma.

224
00:34:55,765 --> 00:34:58,884
She went into a coma during
childbirth.

225
00:34:58,884 --> 00:35:03,196
Meryl was a PVS, persistent
vegetative state, like Lydia, for life.

226
00:35:04,004 --> 00:35:07,163
Her recovery contradicts
everything I am about to say.

227
00:35:07,163 --> 00:35:09,119
That is, that there is hope.

228
00:35:09,483 --> 00:35:11,883
I insist. Scientifically, no.

229
00:35:11,883 --> 00:35:15,034
But if you want to have faith,
OK.

230
00:35:15,323 --> 00:35:18,642
Is she opening her eyes?
Or I imagine this?

231
00:35:18,642 --> 00:35:23,079
She does, but that doesn't mean
she is aware of anything.

232
00:35:23,562 --> 00:35:27,475
Her brain cell has been
completely destroyed.

233
00:35:27,962 --> 00:35:32,591
However, it can control
the automatic functions...

234
00:35:32,961 --> 00:35:37,361
such as breathing, sleeping,
waking up and intestinal functions.

235
00:35:37,361 --> 00:35:40,160
She opens her eyes,
but mechanically.

236
00:35:40,160 --> 00:35:43,436
Her brain is dead. She has
no ideas and feelings.

237
00:35:57,759 --> 00:36:00,148
Come in, please.

238
00:36:11,438 --> 00:36:14,429
-My name is Benigno.
-Marco Zuloaga

239
00:36:14,597 --> 00:36:16,667
This is Alicia.

240
00:36:21,437 --> 00:36:23,836
Was it your first night here?

241
